=== 女性大遊行 ===
{{main|2017年女性大游行}}
女性大游行是自2017年1月21以来在世界各地进行的一系列[[女权|女权]][[游行示威|游行示威]]活动，旨在捍卫[[女权|女权]]，同时为[[移民|移民]]改革、[[科学精神|科学精神]]、[[健保|健保]]改革、[[环境保护|环境保护]]、[[LGBT权益|LGBT权益]]、种族公义、[[世俗化|世俗化]]运动、女性[[堕胎|堕胎]]权益发声。这些游行示威活动直指新任[[美国总统|美国总统]][[唐纳德·特朗普|唐纳德·特朗普]]的一系列言论和立场，包括被指涉及[[性別歧視|性別歧視]]、[[種族歧視|種族歧視]]、[[仇外|仇外]]及[[反伊斯蘭|反伊斯蘭]]等言論。{{efn|此前2005年川普曾夸口言其能在未经允许的情况下抓女性[[生殖器|阴部]]，称“只要你是名人，她們就讓你做，想做什么都行，比如抓她们的下体”。英文原文为“{{lang|en|When you're a star they let you do it, you can do anything, grab 'em by the pussy}}”}}<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-trump-women-idUSKBN1550DW|title=In challenge to Trump, women protesters swarm streets across U.S.|date=2017-01-22|newspaper=Reuters|access-date=2017-01-22|archive-date=2017-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122000623/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-trump-women-idUSKBN1550DW|dead-url=no}}</ref>

其间首次抗议发生于[[华盛顿哥伦比亚特区|华盛顿哥伦比亚特区]]，并被称作'''华盛顿女性大游行'''（{{lang|en|Women's March on Washington}}）。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newyorker.com/culture/jia-tolentino/the-somehow-controversial-womens-march-on-washington|title=The Somehow Controversial Women's March on Washington|last=Tolentino|first=Jia|date=2017-01-18|website=The New Yorker|accessdate=2017-01-20|archive-date=2017-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170120032957/http://www.newyorker.com/culture/jia-tolentino/the-somehow-controversial-womens-march-on-washington|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Bosman|first=Julie|title=In a Rust Belt Town, the Women's March Draws Shrugs and Cheers From Afar|website=[[纽约时报|nytimes]]|date=2017-01-21|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/01/21/us/niles-michigan-trump-no-women-march.html|ref=harv|accessdate=2017-01-22|archive-date=2017-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122030157/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/01/21/us/niles-michigan-trump-no-women-march.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

此次游行示威作为[[草根|草根]]运动在唐纳德·特朗普于同年1月20日[[2017年美國總統就職典禮|就任]]的第二天开始，旨在“向执政当局上台的第一天发出直接信息、告诉世界[[女权即人权|女权即人权]]”、对特朗普的侵犯女性的言论与行为进行抗議。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/01/16/politics/womens-march-on-washington-need-to-know/index.html|title=Women's March on Washington: What you need to know|last=Tatum|first=Sophie|publisher=CNN|date=2017-01-16|access-date=2017-01-20|archive-date=2017-01-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170119234926/http://www.cnn.com/2017/01/16/politics/womens-march-on-washington-need-to-know/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>参与华盛顿游行的人数至少为现场参与前一天就职典礼的人数三倍。<ref name="Wallace">{{cite news|title=Crowd Scientists Say Women's March in Washington Had 3 Times as Many People as Trump's Inauguration|last1=Wallace|first1=Tim|last2=Parlapiano|first2=Alicia|date=2017-01-22|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|accessdate=2017-01-22|url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2017/01/22/us/politics/womens-march-trump-crowd-estimates.html|archive-date=2017-03-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170313210125/https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2017/01/22/us/politics/womens-march-trump-crowd-estimates.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[YouTube|YouTube]]<ref name="YouTube">{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XC9hTrX9oNk&feature=player_embedded |title=Women's March on Washington |accessdate=2017-01-26 |archive-date=2017-01-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122122227/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XC9hTrX9oNk&feature=player_embedded |dead-url=no }}Live stream of Women's March on Washington</ref>、[[Facebook|Facebook]]及[[Twitter|Twitter]]等社交网站上均有直播位於華盛頓的遊行。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.womensmarch.com/ |title=Women's March on Washington |quote=You can view the program live on a number of Jumbotrons on Independence Ave. and through all of our social media platforms, Facebook, Twitter, and YouTube. |website=Women's March |accessdate=2017-01-21 |archive-date=2017-01-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170129062214/https